sentences: Lillie Mae (born Lillie Mae Rische on June 26, 1991) is an American country and Americana singer, songwriter, fiddle and guitar player based out of Nashville, Tennessee.
Lillie Mae and her family toured as a family band for many years.
The family settled in Nashville, Tennessee in 2000.
Most of the siblings signed with Arista Records in 2007 and had two Top 40 singles on Hot Country Songs the next year     "I Don't Love You Like That".

sentences: In 2014, Mae released her first solo song titled "Nobody's".
In 2015 she released Rain On The Piano.
On June 23, 2017, Lillie Mae released Forever and Then Some on Third Man Records.
In 2017, she performed in the multi-award-winning documentary The American Epic Sessions.
She played fiddle and provided background vocals on Jim Lauderdale's 2018 album Time Flies.
On August 16, 2019, Lillie Mae released her follow up studio album, Other Girls on Third Man Records.
